commit.message:
feat: migrate to DynamoDB

Most of the APIs have been updated to use DynamoDB instead of MySQL.
The service worker still needs to updated with this information.

fix: add check for empty list

added a check for empty lists that are sent into the findName function
in the List class.

fix: filter for match chats

fixed the filter function for matches for the search bar.

fix: error message for mobile view

Error messages were not fitted to the screens of mobile devices,
so I added in a media query to fix this issue.

feat: user cannot match their pet

Owners should not get their pets in their own search results.

fix: update state of owner

owner's name now updates...:D

feat: moved pets into its own store

Moved the pets list into its own store for persistance of data.

fix: calendar rendering fix

The month of february wasnt being generated correctly, so it's been fixed.

fix: initial page load

I needed to adjust the initial page load for the app to the landing
page content and not the dummy content.

fix: update entire month on calendar

The month was not updating when a user would click through their calendar.

feat: messages order by date

Messages were not ordered by date, and now they are.

chore: update database diagram

I updated the database diagram to match the current version of the
model/controllers.

feat: service worker GET fully works offline

SW works offline for all GET requests to Furbabies APIs.

feat: form message validation

Added form validation for messages and play date in the chat feature.

feat: all matches show up per user's account

Users can now access their matches and chat messages offline.
Next is the calendar...and then clearing IDB upon login...and logout.

feat: service worker chat messages

User chat messages appear, but now I need to get match url to match
correctly.

feat: service worker for user and pet profiles

Pet and user profiles work offline...meaning they display offline...
you cannot edit anything yet.

style: profile class for tablets

Added another media query for tablet viewport sizes. The current
media query was not enough to make it not look squished.

chore: compile react components

I forgot to compile the react components from the last commit,
so adding that in right now.

fix: loader displayed at proper times

The loader seemed to be kinda random when it would appear to users,
so went through and figured out exactly where it should be displayed.

feat: update about component

The about page was laking in detail, so I updated it to be a little
more attractive and simplistic in describing the web app.

fix: update image carousel position

If a user deleted the last element in a list longer than 1 element,
the app would crash creating and throw an error. So, I updated the
position to the beginning of the list instead of the current image
that was deleted.

feat: today's agenda updates

In the calendar feature, users had to click away to update the agenda.
Now, today's agenda is updated upload initial load.

fix: iOS image carousel

The image carousel was not formatted properly due to iOS default values,
so added custom values to override default values for buttons.

I, also, removed the actions directory, because it was just taking up space.
chore: update README.md for Hackathon

feat: remove user images

Users can now remove images from their profile as well as their
pets' profiles.

style: update mobile view

Tweeked a lot of the mobile view styles to fix IOS issues.

style: add media query for login/profile

Media queries have been added to login and profile for better
a better experience on mobile devices.

feat: users can accept playdates

Users can finally accept playdates!! :D
THE APP IS PRETTY MUCH DONE!

TODO:
- media query for profile component
- delete images
* security?

feat: propose playdate

Users can now propose playdates, but there were also a lot of bug
fixes with queries that needed to be corrected.
